
spring.datasource.url=jdbc:postgresql://${DB_HOST}:${DB_PORT}/${DB_NAME}
spring.datasource.username=${DB_USERNAME}
spring.datasource.password=${DB_PASS}







Create all needed packages, classes, e.t.c with tdd

MODELS

User - id, first_name, last_name, email, phone_number, address, password, accounts, credit_transactions, debit_transactions
Account - id, user, account_name, account_type, account_number, account_balance
CreditTransactions - id, recipient, sender, sender_account, recipient_account, amount, timestamp, credit_channel
DebitTransactions - id, debited_account, debit_channel, amount
Logs - id, source_class_name, event_description


CONTROLLERS

UserController - CRUD
AccountController - CRUD
CreditTransactionsController - CRUD
DebitTransactionsController - CRUD
RobotCpuController - CRUD

REPOSITORIES
UserRepository
AccountRepository
CreditTransactionRepository
DebitTransactionsRepository
LogsRepository


SERVICES
UserService - CRUD 
AccountService - CRUD
CreditTransactionsService - CRUD
DebitTransactionsService - CRUD
RobotCpuService - CRUD
LoggingService
AlertService


Auth


SecurityConfig
CustomUserDetailsService
AuthenticationFilter
AuthorizationFilter




